  ('FAR', 'Shareholders'' Equity & Share-Based Payment',
   'When delinquent subscribed shares are sold at public auction, the shares are awarded to the bidder willing to pay the total amount due for:',
   'The smallest number of shares', 'The largest number of shares', 'The shares with the highest par value', 'Half of the subscribed shares',
   0, 'The highest bidder in a delinquency sale is the one willing to take the SMALLEST number of shares in exchange for paying the full balance due plus accrued interest and the costs of sale; remaining shares go to the delinquent subscriber.', 2),
  ('FAR', 'Shareholders'' Equity & Share-Based Payment',
   'A 2-for-1 share split:',
   'Doubles total share capital', 'Requires a transfer from retained earnings to share capital', 'Is recorded by a memorandum entry only, halving par value per share with no change in total equity', 'Increases share premium',
   2, 'A split increases the number of shares and proportionately reduces par (or stated) value, leaving share capital and total equity unchanged — only a memo entry is needed. A share dividend, in contrast, capitalizes retained earnings.', 1),
  ('FAR', 'Shareholders'' Equity & Share-Based Payment',
   'An entity declared noncash assets (equipment) as a property dividend. The dividend payable is measured at:',
   'The carrying amount of the equipment at declaration date', 'The par value of the shares held by the recipients', 'The original cost of the equipment', 'The fair value of the equipment, remeasured at each reporting date and at settlement, with changes recognized in equity',
   3, 'Under IFRIC 17, a dividend payable of noncash assets is measured at the fair value of the assets to be distributed, remeasured through equity until settlement; on settlement, the difference between the payable and the assets'' carrying amount goes to profit or loss.', 3),
  ('FAR', 'Shareholders'' Equity & Share-Based Payment',
   'An appropriation of retained earnings for plant expansion:',
   'Sets aside cash for the expansion', 'Reduces total retained earnings and total equity', 'Reduces unappropriated retained earnings but leaves total retained earnings and total equity unchanged', 'Is recognized as a liability',
