   'P38', 'P41', 'P44', 'P55',
   2, 'Preference equity = 10,000 × P110 liquidation value = P1,100,000. Ordinary equity = P5,500,000 − P1,100,000 = P4,400,000 ÷ 100,000 shares = P44 per share.', 3),
  ('FAR', 'Shareholders'' Equity & Share-Based Payment',
   'Convertible bonds were issued for total proceeds of P5,000,000. The fair value of similar bonds without the conversion feature is P4,600,000. At issuance, the amount credited to equity is:',
   'P0', 'P200,000', 'P400,000', 'P5,000,000',
   2, 'Compound instruments are split using the with-and-without method: the liability component is the fair value of a comparable bond without the equity feature (P4,600,000), and the residual P400,000 is the equity (conversion option) component. The split is never revised.', 2),
  ('FAR', 'Shareholders'' Equity & Share-Based Payment',
