  ('FAR', 'Shareholders'' Equity & Share-Based Payment',
   'Share appreciation rights payable in cash are accounted for as:',
   'An equity-settled share-based payment measured at grant date only', 'An expense only when exercised', 'A memorandum entry until exercise', 'A liability remeasured at fair value at each reporting date until settlement, with changes recognized in profit or loss',
   3, 'Cash-settled share-based payments create a liability measured at the fair value of the SARs, remeasured every reporting date and at settlement, with fair value changes in profit or loss — unlike equity-settled awards, which are fixed at grant-date fair value.', 2),
  ('FAR', 'Shareholders'' Equity & Share-Based Payment',
   'A share option grant vests only if the entity''s share price reaches a specified level (a market condition). If employees complete the service period but the share price target is not met:',
   'Compensation expense is still recognized, because market conditions are reflected in the grant-date fair value and not subsequently trued up', 'All previously recognized expense is reversed', 'No expense is ever recognized for the grant', 'The expense is reclassified to OCI',
   0, 'Market conditions are incorporated into the grant-date fair value measurement; expense is recognized if service (and non-market) conditions are met, regardless of whether the market condition is achieved. Only failures of service/non-market conditions trigger reversal.', 3),
  ('FAR', 'Revenue Recognition (PFRS 15)',
   'An entity received cash from a customer, but the arrangement does not yet meet the PFRS 15 criteria for a contract (collectibility is not probable). The cash received is:',
   'Recognized as revenue immediately', 'Recognized as revenue using the installment method', 'Recognized as a liability until the criteria are met, the entity has no remaining obligations, or the contract is terminated', 'Credited to OCI',
   2, 'When contract criteria are unmet, consideration received is a liability. Revenue is recognized only when the criteria are subsequently met, or when the consideration is nonrefundable and the entity has fully performed or the contract is terminated.', 2),
  ('FAR', 'Revenue Recognition (PFRS 15)',
   'A promised good or service is distinct — and therefore a separate performance obligation — when:',
   'It is physically delivered separately from other goods', 'The customer can benefit from it on its own or with readily available resources, AND it is separately identifiable from other promises in the contract', 'It has a standalone selling price in any market', 'It is invoiced as a separate line item',
   1, 'Both criteria must be met: capable of being distinct (benefit on its own or with readily available resources) and distinct within the context of the contract (not an input to a combined output, not highly interdependent).', 2),
  ('FAR', 'Revenue Recognition (PFRS 15)',
   'An entity need not adjust the transaction price for a significant financing component when:',
   'The customer pays in cash rather than on credit', 'The financing rate is below the market rate', 'The contract price is fixed', 'At contract inception, the expected period between the transfer of goods and the customer''s payment is one year or less',
   3, 'PFRS 15 provides a practical expedient: no adjustment for the time value of money when the gap between performance and payment is expected to be one year or less at inception.', 2),
  ('FAR', 'Revenue Recognition (PFRS 15)',
   'In a bill-and-hold arrangement, the seller may recognize revenue before physical delivery when:',
   'The reason for the arrangement is substantive, the goods are separately identified as the customer''s, are ready for transfer, and the seller cannot use or redirect them', 'The customer has paid at least half of the price', 'The goods are expected to be shipped within the next quarter', 'The seller obtains insurance over the goods',
   0, 'Revenue requires the customer to have obtained control despite the seller''s physical possession — demonstrated by the four bill-and-hold criteria. Custodial services may be a separate performance obligation.', 3),
  ('FAR', 'Revenue Recognition (PFRS 15)',
   'An entity sells goods with a right of return. At the point of sale, the entity recognizes:',
   'Revenue for the full amount, with returns expensed when they occur', 'No revenue until the return period lapses', 'Revenue only for the consideration it expects to be entitled to, a refund liability for expected returns, and an asset for the right to recover the goods', 'A provision equal to the gross sales price',
   2, 'Expected returns are variable consideration: revenue is constrained to the expected entitled amount, a refund liability captures expected refunds, and a return asset (measured at former carrying amount less recovery costs) reflects the goods to be recovered.', 2),
  ('FAR', 'Revenue Recognition (PFRS 15)',
   'A consignor recognizes revenue on goods delivered to a consignee (dealer):',
   'Upon shipment to the consignee', 'When the consignee sells the goods to the end customer', 'When the consignment agreement is signed', 'Thirty days after delivery to the consignee',
   1, 'In a consignment, the dealer does not obtain control of the goods on delivery — the consignor retains control until sale to the end customer (or expiry of the consignment period), so revenue is deferred until that point.', 1),
  ('FAR', 'Revenue Recognition (PFRS 15)',
   'A franchise license that provides the customer the right to ACCESS the franchisor''s intellectual property as it evolves over the license period (e.g., an evolving brand and system) results in revenue recognized:',
   'At the point in time the license period begins', 'When the initial franchise fee is collected', 'Upon signing of the franchise agreement', 'Over time, throughout the license period',
   3, 'A right-to-access license (symbolic IP that the franchisor''s activities continue to affect) is a performance obligation satisfied over time. A right-to-use license (functional IP as it exists at grant) is satisfied at a point in time.', 2),
  ('FAR', 'Revenue Recognition (PFRS 15)',
   'An entity has satisfied a performance obligation but its right to the consideration is conditional on satisfying another performance obligation in the contract. The entity recognizes:',
   'A contract asset', 'An account receivable', 'Deferred revenue', 'An unbilled contingent asset disclosed only',
   0, 'A contract asset is a right to consideration conditioned on something other than the passage of time (e.g., further performance). Once the right becomes unconditional, it is reclassified to receivable.', 2),
  ('FAR', 'Cash Flows, Interim, Segment & Other Topics',
   'Sales for the year were P8,000,000. Accounts receivable were P1,200,000 at the beginning of the year and P1,500,000 at year-end. Cash collected from customers under the direct method is:',
   'P7,700,000', 'P8,000,000', 'P8,300,000', 'P9,500,000',
   0, 'Collections = sales + beginning AR − ending AR = P8,000,000 + P1,200,000 − P1,500,000 = P7,700,000. The P300,000 increase in receivables represents sales not yet collected.', 2),
  ('FAR', 'Cash Flows, Interim, Segment & Other Topics',
   'A noncurrent asset classified as held for sale under PFRS 5 is measured at:',
   'Fair value less costs to sell in all cases', 'The lower of its carrying amount and fair value less costs to sell, with depreciation ceasing', 'Carrying amount, with continued depreciation', 'Value in use',
   1, 'Held-for-sale assets are measured at the lower of carrying amount and fair value less costs to sell, presented separately as current, and are no longer depreciated while so classified.', 2),
  ('FAR', 'Cash Flows, Interim, Segment & Other Topics',
   'Under PAS 7, dividends PAID by a non-financial entity may be classified in the statement of cash flows as:',
   'Operating or investing activities', 'Investing activities only', 'Financing activities, or alternatively operating activities', 'Investing or financing activities',
   2, 'Dividends paid may be shown as financing (cost of obtaining financial resources) or as operating (to help users assess the ability to pay dividends from operating cash flows), applied consistently. Dividends received may be operating or investing.', 2)
